<!--Appication Layout-->
<a class="anchor" id="Application-Layout"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>1. Application Layout</h3>
    <p>
        The common application layout components consists of the navigation bar located at the top of the page and the footer.
        To naviagate around the main areas of the application you can use the naviagation bar located at the top of the screen.
        This contains links to the Home, Create, Search, About Us, Contact Us, Log In and Register screens. 
        There is also a "Tweet" button located above the log in section of the naviagtion bar. 
        This is used to allow people to tweet LookItUp's URL and increase the LookItUp community through social media.
        The footer contains a link to the online user manual and a manage account screen.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/layoutScreen.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>

<!--Home Screen-->
<a class="anchor" id="Home-Screen"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>2. Home Sceen</h3>
    <p>
        The home screen is the first point of contect users have with the application. 
        It gives a brief overview of what the application can do and then lists links to the main functionality areas on the left side.
        On the right side the last three businesses that were added or updated are displayed.
    </p>
    <p>
        
        You can use the blue links provided on the left side of the home screen to access important sections of the application i.e. Search, Create, Register or Log In.
        The right hand side of the page displays a brief overview of the last three businesses that were added or updated.
        The rating displayed underneath the business represents the average rating the business has received when users reviewed it. 
        A user can view a business by clicking on the business name.
    </p>

    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/homeScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Searching For A Business-->
<a class="anchor" id="Searching-Businesses"></a>

<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>3. Searching For A Business</h3>
    <p>
        When the search page is visited you will be displayed with filter options on the top of the screen and a list of 20 businesses currently stored within the database.
    </p>
    <p>
        In order to filter through businesses to find the one you are looking for you can use the fields provided.
        These fields include the category of the business, the county the business is in and the name of the business.
        You can fill in these fields as relevant to the business you are searching for and click on the filter button to find a business. 
        For example if you want to find a Subway in Dublin you could enter: Category = "Food and Dining", County = "Dublin" and Name = "Subway" and then click the filter button.
        The first 20 results of the query would then be displayed and you can choose which Subway in Dublin you would like to view information about.
        If the business does not exist and the search query is empty you are then prompted to add the business yourself to improve the applciations collection of businesses and help the community.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/searchScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000"><br /> <br />
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/searchScreen2.png" height="300" width="600">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Creating A Business-->
<a class="anchor" id="Creating-Businesses"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>4. Creating A Business</h3>
    <p>
        To create a business click the create button in the navigation bar.
        This will display the create business screen where you can enter the details of the business you want to add.
        The details you enter on this page are the business name, street, town, county and a description.
        There is an anti-spam CAPTCHA on this page that needs to filled in.
        Once you have finished entering the business details click the create button and the business will be added to the database.
        This is a speedy way to create a business without the need to fill in a long form. 
        Once a business is created you can upadate the details and enter a lot more information about the business.
    </p>
    <b>Errors Creating A Business</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/createScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Viewing A Business-->
<a class="anchor" id="Viewing-Businesses"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>5. Viewing A Business</h3>
    <p>
        To view a businesses details you can locate a business listed on the right side of the home page or in the search screen. 
        Once you have found a business that you want to view, click on the business name and you will be brought to the business details screen.
        This lists the basic business details such as the business name, the average review rating and the location on the top of the screen.
        Below you will find an image gallery that shows the photos that have been uploaded.
        There is also business deails such as the address, category of business, price rating, contact details, a description of the business and much more.
        The business location is also displayed on a map below the details using Google Maps (The location is based on the text address entered above and may not always be precise if the address is inaccurate).
        Finally all of the user reviews are listed at the bottom of the page, these include the users rating and a decription of their experience.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/detailsScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000"><br /><br />
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/detailsScreen3.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Editing A Business-->
<a class="anchor" id="Editing-Businesses"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>6. Editing A Business</h3>
    <p>
        To edit a businesses details you must click on a businesses name to select the business and then click on the "Add/Edit businesses details" link located at the top of the business details page.
        If you are logged in you will see the edit screen or if you are not then you will be asked to login.
        Once on the edit screen you can enter additional business details and upload images.
    </p>
    <p>
        The left side of the screen has the business details that you can edit.
        The image uploader is located on the right side of the screen.
        To upload an image click the browse button and locate the desired image to upload (Note: the .jpeg is currently the only supported format, this will be changed to support more formats soon).
        If there are any images currently associated with the business they will appear beside the "Current Photo:" section.
        If you want to overwrite an image simply click the browse button on a photo that is already has an image associated with it and select another image.
        When you have finished editing details of the business click the save button and then details will be saved to the database.
    </p>
    <b>Errors Editing A Business</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/editBusinessScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/editBusinessScreen2.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Writing A Review-->
<a class="anchor" id="Writing-Reviews"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>7. Writing A Review</h3>
    <p>
        To write a review click onto the business that you want to review and then scroll to the review section and click the "Write A Review" link.
        This will bring you to the screen where you may write a review.
        You may write a review description and give it a score from 0-10, this score will affect the rating showed at the top of the business details page.
        Once you have finished writing your review click the create button.
    </p>
     <b>Errors when writing reviews</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
        If you try to enter a rating greater than 10 or less than 0 you will be prompted to change the value to one within the acceptable range.
        If you have already reviewed the business then an error will be displayed stating that you can only review a business once.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/writeReview1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Editing A Review-->
<a class="anchor" id="Editing-Reviews"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>8. Editing A Review</h3>
    <p>
        To edit a review find a review that you have written located on the business details page and click the edit button located beneth it.
        Change the review details and rating as you wish and click the save button.
    </p>
    <b>Errors when writing reviews</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
        If you try to edit somebody elses review you will be shown an error stating that you can only edit your own reviews.
        If you try enter a rating greater that 10 or less than 0 you will be shown an error with the acceptable range (0 - 10).
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/editReview1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Deleting A Review-->
<a class="anchor" id="Deleting-Reviews"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>9. Deleteing A Review</h3>
    <p>
        To delete a review locate a review that you have written on the business details screen and click the delete button below.
        The confirm delete screen will then be displayed containing the details of the review.
        If you are sure you want to delete the review click the delete buttton and the review will be erased.
    </p>
    <b>Errors Deleting A Review</b>
    <p>
        If you try to delete somebody else's review you will be shown an error stating that you can only delete your own reviews.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/deleteReview1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--About Us-->
<a class="anchor" id="About-Us"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>10. About Us</h3>
    <p>
        The "About Us" section shows information about the applciation developer and the application itself.
        This screen is solely used to convey information about LookItUp to the user and therefore there is no functionality required.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/aboutUsScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Contacting Us-->
<a class="anchor" id="Contact-Us"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>11. Contacting Us</h3>
    <p>
        The Contact Us screen has a contact form that directly emails the developer of the appliciation.
        All section of the form must be filled in before it can be sent.
        It is reccommended that the subject field contain a brief overview of the subject matter of the email e.g. "Bug", "Report A Business", "Feedback" etc.
        Once the form is filled in you can fill in the CAPTCHA fields and press send message.
        You should then be shown a confirmation screen to show the message was sent successfully.
    </p>
    <b>Errors Sending Email</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
        If the email address is not valid an error will be displayed on screen.
        If the CAPTCHA is wrong the box will trun red and the user can then re-enter the correct CAPTCHA details.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/contactUs1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Register Account-->
<a class="anchor" id="Register-Account"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>12. Register For An Account</h3>
    <p>
        To register for an account you must select the register tab located on the navigation bar.
        Once on the the register page you must enter your desired username, a password (minimum 6 characteters long) and confirm the password. 
        You must then fill in an anti-spam CAPTCHA and click the register button.
    </p>
    <b>Errors Register For An Account</b>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
        If the username you have chosen is not available, a message will be displayed stating that, you can then select an alternative username and try again.
        If the password and the confirm password field do not match, you must re-enter both fields, then click the register button.
        If the password is less than 6 characters in length, you must enter a new password that is 6 or more characters in lenght.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/registerScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />

<!--Manage Account-->
<a class="anchor" id="Managing-Account"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>13. Managing Your Account</h3>
    <p>
        To manage your account click the Manage Account link located on the bottom of the screen. 
        In order to access this screen you must be logged in.
        This screen allows you to change the password on your account, you may do so by entering your current password, your new password and then confirming your new password.
        Once your details are entered click the "Change Password" button and your details will be changed.
        A confirmation message will be displayed on screen to confirm your password was changed.
    </p>
    <p>
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
        If the new password is not 6 characters long the password will not be changed and "The New password must be at least 6 characters long." will be displayed on screen.
        If the new password and the confirm password do not match then "The new password and confirmation password do not match." will be displayed on screen.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/accountScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />


<!--Log In Account-->
<a class="anchor" id="LogIn-Account"></a>
<div class="text-justify">
    <h3>14. Log Into Your Account</h3>
    <p>
        To log into the application click the log in button located on the navigation bar.
        Once on the log in screen users can enter their username and password. 
        If you wish to have the browser remember your details you can select the "Remeber Me" checkbox.
        You can then click log in and  you will be logged in and can access the restricted parts of the application.

    </p>
    <b>Errors Logging Into Your Account</b>
    <p>
        If the log in is unsuccessful a message will be displayed stating the username or password was incorrect and you can attempt to log in again.
        If any of the fields are left blank then you will be shown an error stating that the field specified field cannot be blank.
    </p>
    <img class="manualImage" src="/Images/UserManual/logInScreen1.png" height="600" width="1000">
</div>
<hr />